text.tspan: Dear Hiring Manager,
Hi there, I’m Ashley. I’m currently in my third and last year at George
Brown College in Toronto, Ontario studying Interaction Design and
Development. I saw your posting for a Winter 2021 front-end software
development intern on LinkedIn, and I felt that I fit the bill perfectly. My
interests lie in developing interfaces and I intend to build a career in
front-end development. I am familiar with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript,
which I have used for the past two years to create web pages that both
look good and are user-friendly. Most importantly, I am passionate about
expanding my understanding of technologies and coding frameworks.
My approach to coding, design, and everything in between is that there is
no problem that cannot be solved with a little bit of time and effort. For a
major term project, I was tasked with simulating the inherent lack of
privacy in a city, and a professor suggested an open-source object
detection system called YOLO that could generate the feeling of being
watched. Given that I had never heard of it, had zero experience with
Python, and had limited time, getting it to work seemed almost
impossible. And yet, with a lot of determination and a massive, massive
amount of troubleshooting, I was able to apply the system to two videos
and achieve what I had intended.
As a student, I see no better way to learn about front-end development
than from an industry leader. I am confident that I can contribute to your
company’s ethos of eagerly tackling the challenges of making your clients’
user experience an easy one through code.
Please feel free to contact me at the phone number or email listed above,
and I hope to hear from you soon.
Thank you,
Ashley Lall
